def view(column):
    '''
       .
    
       ( )   'data'.
          .
    
    '''

    plt.figure(figsize=(7, 2))
    plt.title(label=f'   \n{column}')

    plt.xlabel(' ')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.show()

def show_na():
    '''
       .
    
        ,
       .
    
    '''

    total = data.isna().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    percent = (data.isna().sum() /
               data.isna().count() * 100).round(1).sort_values(ascending=False)
    display(pd.concat([total, percent], axis=1, keys=[' ', '%']))

def fill_by_mode(column):
    '''
         (  ).
    
       ().
      ,    
         brand  model.
    
    '''

    for brand in data.loc[data[column].isna(), 'brand'].unique():
        for model in data.loc[
            data[column].isna()
            & (data['brand'] == brand),
            'model'].unique():

            mode_value = data.loc[
                data[column].notna()
                & (data['brand'] == brand)
                & (data['model'] == model),
                column].mode()

            if len(mode_value) == 1:
                data.loc[
                    data[column].isna()
                    & (data['brand'] == brand)
                    & (data['model'] == model),
                    column] = mode_value[0]

for brand in data.loc[data['power'].isna(), 'brand'].unique():
    for model in data.loc[

        'model'].unique():

        median_value = data.loc[
            data['power'].notna()
            & (data['brand'] == brand)
            & (data['model'] == model),
            'power'].median()

        data.loc[
            data['power'].isna()
            & (data['brand'] == brand)
            & (data['model'] == model),
            'power'] = median_value

def cv_score(model, X=features_train, y=target_train):
    '''
        (RMSE) ,
       -.
    
        
    ( -  ).
         (RMSE).
    
    '''

    return abs(cross_val_score(model, X=X, y=y,
                               cv=CV, n_jobs=-1, error_score='raise',
                               scoring=SCORER).mean())

parameters = {'n_estimators': [10, 20, 50, 100, 200, 500, 1000],
              'learning_rate':
               [0.005, 0.01, 0.05]+[0.1*n for n in range(1, 10)]}

catboost = RandomizedSearchCV(
    model_catboost,
    param_distributions=parameters,
    cv=CV,
    n_iter=10,
    scoring=SCORER,
    random_state=RANDOM_STATE,
    n_jobs=-1,
    error_score='raise')

catboost.fit(features_cat_train, target_train)

print('      CatBoost')
print('\nRMSE =', round(abs(catboost.best_score_)), '')
print('\n  :',
      pd.DataFrame(catboost.best_params_, index = ['']).T)
